<doc id="453763" wikidata="Q1810140" url="?curid=453763" title="List of contemporary artists">
<text>This is a list of artists who create contemporary art, i.e., those whose peak of activity can be situated somewhere between the 1970s (the advent of postmodernism) and the present day. Artists on this list meet the following criteria:
*The person is regarded as an important figure or is widely cited by his/her peers or successors.
*The person is known for originating a significant new concept, theory or technique.
*The person has created, or played a major role in co-creating, a significant or well-known work, or collective body of work, that has been the subject of an independent book or feature-length film, or of multiple independent periodical articles or reviews.
*The person&#x27;s work either (a) has become a significant monument, (b) has been a substantial part of a significant exhibition, (c) has won significant critical attention, or (d) is represented within the permanent collections of several notable galleries or museums, or had works in many significant libraries.


==A==
* Martine Aballéa (born 1950), installation artist
* Marina Abramović (born 1946), performance artist
* Vito Acconci (1940–2017), installation and performance artist
* Rita Ackermann (born 1968), artist
