<doc id="453977" wikidata="Q7133563" url="?curid=453977" title="Paqarina">
<text>Paqarina is a Quechua term that ancient Andeans used to describe the place of origin, and final destination, of their ancestors. &quot;Paqarinas&quot; were associated with physical landmarks such as holes in the ground or lakes. In Incan mythology the word also describes a type of &quot;portal&quot; through which the forces of life and death flow.

